sentences: Levy began his full-time college teaching career at Towson State University in late 1967 creating "The Towson State Jazz Ensemble".
section: == Life and career ==

sentences: By 1970, his hard work and passion for teaching brought the band to national prominence when his Towson State Jazz Ensemble competed and won the outstanding band honors at the Notre Dame Collegiate Jazz Festival.
section: == Life and career ==

sentences: He was posthumously honored by Towson University in a ceremony on April 13, 2017.
section: == Life and career ==

sentences: Levy died of congestive heart failure in Parkville, Maryland, aged 73, on September 18, 2001.

sentences: Henry Jacob "Hank" Levy (September 27, 1927 – September 18, 2001) was an American jazz composer and saxophonist whose works often employed unusual time signatures.
In his last years, he more frequently turned to bebop originals, tunes by Charlie Parker, Dizzy Gillespie, Tadd Dameron.
